@shirisht

I think reorganizing the docs to have an Execution Modes section is an excellent idea. There is a lot of value to that idea. Perhaps I can do that as a separate PR since reorganizing seems like a separate unit of work.

With regards to the **DML and PyDML Programming Guide**, I created it for a complete beginner to start becoming familiar with the absolute basics of the language (data types, matrix indexing, control statements, etc) rather than being a guide for ML. It should probably be renamed to something like **Beginner's Guide to DML and PyDML** or **Language Basics** or something like that. I think you are right in that a **DML and PyDML Programming Guide** should detail practices such as writing efficient ML code that scales. I can put something like this together if I can get lots of input from the ML experts on the project.

@shirisht, @deroneriksson,
Addressed your comments in the commit 8604ce40efedd393b29070249f22c07f8a5f7a65
could you take a look?
